const canvas = document.getElementById('gameCanvas');
const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
let snake = [{x: 100, y: 100}];
let food = {x: 300, y: 300};
let direction = 'right';
let score = 0;

// Game loop
function gameLoop() {
    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);

    // Move snake
    let newHead = {x: snake[0].x + (direction === 'left' ? -1 : 1), y: snake[0].y};
    snake.unshift(newHead);

    // Check for collision with food
    if (snake[0].x === food.x && snake[0].y === food.y) {
        score += 10;
        food = {x: Math.floor(Math.random() * 390), y: Math.floor(Math.random() * 390)};
    }

    // Check for collision with walls
    if (snake[0].x < 0 || snake[0].x >= canvas.width || snake[0].y < 0 || snake[0].y >= canvas.height) {
        clearInterval(gameLoop);
        return;
    }

    // Draw snake
    snake.forEach((part, index) => {
        ctx.fillStyle = '#ff0000';
        if (index === 0) { ctx.fillRect(part.x - 10, part.y - 10, 20, 20); }
        else { ctx.fillRect(part.x, part.y, 20, 20);
    });

    // Draw food
    ctx.fillStyle = '#ff0000';
    if (snake[0].x === food.x && snake[0].y === food.y) {
        ctx.fillRect(food.x - 10, food.y - 10, 20, 20);
    }

    // Check for collision with itself
    for (let i = 0; i < snake.length - 1; i++) {
        if (snake[i].x === snake[1].x && snake[i].y === snake[1].y) {
            clearInterval(gameLoop);
            return;
        }
    }

    // Update direction based on arrow keys
    document.addEventListener('keydown', e => {
        if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') { direction = 'left'; }
        else if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') { direction = 'right'; }
        else if (e.key === 'ArrowUp') { direction = 'up'; }
        else if (e.key === 'ArrowDown') { direction = 'down'; }
    });

    // Game loop
    gameLoop();
</script>
